    RANDOM MODULE  
    =============

=> sudo random numebr generators 
=> https://www.askpython.com/python-modules/python-random-module-generate-random-numbers-sequences
=> random.randrange(i, j), random.randint(100, 200), random.random(), random.choice()
    e.g 
print(random.randrange(1, 5)
print(random.randint(100, 200))


    PYTHON LISTS
    ============
=> is a data structre, is like array in JS
    e.g 
        fruits_list = ["apple", "banana", "mango"]
=> concept of index, offset and addpending items to list 
=> first index 0 because it has 0 offset 
=> to change the value of item at particular index is by 
        list[index] = "new_value"
=> list.append("value"): adds new item to end of list 
=> list.extend("value1", "value2",..): adds new items to the list

    INDEX ERROS AND NESTED LISTS 
    ============================
=> indexError: happens when one tries to access the element outside of range 
        i.e if total max index is 10 and you try to get 11th index item
=> nested lists: when one list contains multiple lists within itself 
    e.g 
        boys_list = ["ram", "shyam", "hari"]
        girls_list = ["rita", "sita", "gita"]
        nested_list = [boys_list, girls_list] 
            i.e: [["ram", "shyam", "hari"],["rita", "sita", "gita"]]

    LOOPS IN PYTHON 
    ============================

=> for in loop to access the list elements
    e.g
        lists = ["item1", "item2", "item3"]
        for item in lists
            print(item)
=> for in loop  with range 
    e.g
        for n in range(0, 10, steps))
        # steps is used as diff between consecutive nums
=> sum(), max(), min() 

